<span id="freeTextContainer5116789802092277832">This is nearly a guide for Christians confused/scared about being Christian and gay. I know it has &quot;God&quot; in the title, but it was really, really Bible heavy. A step-by-step guide through all the oft-quoted and debated passages.<br/><br/>In other words, not meant for me at all and, and therefore, quite boring. The poor kid goes over and over the same questions in his head, taking forever to do what needs to be done. Realistic, but not interesting. My edition had two boys holding hands on the cover, and tho</span>
  <span id="freeText5116789802092277832" style="display:none">This is nearly a guide for Christians confused/scared about being Christian and gay. I know it has "God" in the title, but it was really, really Bible heavy. A step-by-step guide through all the oft-quoted and debated passages.<br /><br />In other words, not meant for me at all and, and therefore, quite boring. The poor kid goes over and over the same questions in his head, taking forever to do what needs to be done. Realistic, but not interesting. My edition had two boys holding hands on the cover, and those are the stories we need, but that cover isn't really this book.<br /><br />If I had been a Christian gay boy a dozen years ago, this book might have saved my life. As it is, I barely made it through the thing.</span>
