  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_213808722" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/213808722" />
    <a title="Phil Ansell" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5612096-phil-ansell"><img alt="Phil Ansell" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1516645204p2/5612096.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/213808722?book_show_action=true">Sep 23, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Phil Ansell" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Phil Ansell" href="/user/show/5612096-phil-ansell">Phil Ansell</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/10054380-the-god-box">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5612096-phil-ansell?shelf=favourites">favourites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5612096-phil-ansell?shelf=m-m-romance">m-m-romance</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer213808722" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8051950651753338511">Fantastic!! Alex Sanchez tells a touching story of Paul, a Christian teenager who is really struggling with his confusing and developing homosexual feelings. His world is opened and challenged when he meets out and proud teenager Manuel.<br/><br/>The story is brilliant and wonderfully written but what I absolutely loved was how Alex Sanchez addressed and challenged pretty much every Bible passage that appears to condemn homosexuality, and especially those that the Church and certain Christian groups use a</span>
  <span id="freeText8051950651753338511" style="display:none">Fantastic!! Alex Sanchez tells a touching story of Paul, a Christian teenager who is really struggling with his confusing and developing homosexual feelings. His world is opened and challenged when he meets out and proud teenager Manuel.<br /><br />The story is brilliant and wonderfully written but what I absolutely loved was how Alex Sanchez addressed and challenged pretty much every Bible passage that appears to condemn homosexuality, and especially those that the Church and certain Christian groups use against gay people. I fully believe that every Christian needs to read this book! It gives you a full sense of what it means to be loving and accepting, exactly what Jesus wants us to be. <br /><br />Anyone who is, or has, ever struggled with coming out or accepting themselves for who they are then this book shows you that you are certainly not alone and gives a wonderful message of hope.<br />If you are struggling with being gay and Christian then don't hesitate to pick it up.<br /><br />I personally got a lot out of this book both academically and spiritually, and in terms of entertainment it was engaging and moving. I absolutely loved it. Thank you Alex Sanchez for writing this, I will certainly be checking out more of your books.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8051950651753338511" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

